  "prompt": "Where do I download Quora for Windows 10?",
  "response": "You can download Quora for Windows 10 through the Microsoft Store. Here are the steps to do so:\n\n1. **Open the Microsoft Store**:\n   - Click on the Start menu and type \"Microsoft Store\" in the search bar, then open the app.\n\n2. **Search for Quora**:\n   - In the Microsoft Store, use the search bar at the top right corner and type \"Quora.\"\n\n3. **Select the Quora App**:\n   - Find the Quora app in the search results and click on it to open the app's page.\n\n4. **Download and Install**:\n   - On the Quora app's page, click the \"Get\" or \"Install\" button. The app will download and install automatically on your Windows 10 device.\n\nAlternatively, you can also access Quora through a web browser by visiting [www.quora.com](https://www.quora.com), which does not require any download or installation.\n\nIf you prefer to use the desktop version of Quora, the Microsoft Store is the safest and most straightforward way to get the app for Windows 10.",
